Implement --quiet and --verbose flags to control output verbosity across all commands.

## File: src/output/verbosity.rs

### Verbosity Levels
```rust
#[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, PartialOrd, Ord, Debug, Default)]
pub enum Verbosity {
    Quiet,    // -q: Only errors, no progress
    #[default]
    Normal,   // Default: Normal output
    Verbose,  // -v: Extra details
    Debug,    // -vv: Debug output (enables tracing)
}

impl Verbosity {
    pub fn from_flags(quiet: bool, verbose_count: u8) -> Self {
        if quiet {
            Self::Quiet
        } else {
            match verbose_count {
                0 => Self::Normal,
                1 => Self::Verbose,
                _ => Self::Debug,
            }
        }
    }

    /// Returns the tracing log level for this verbosity
    pub fn log_level(&self) -> tracing::Level {
        match self {
            Self::Quiet => tracing::Level::ERROR,
            Self::Normal => tracing::Level::WARN,
            Self::Verbose => tracing::Level::INFO,
            Self::Debug => tracing::Level::DEBUG,
        }
    }

    /// Returns tracing filter directive string
    pub fn log_filter(&self) -> &'static str {
        match self {
            Self::Quiet => "error",
            Self::Normal => "warn",
            Self::Verbose => "info",
            Self::Debug => "debug",
        }
    }
}

impl Output {
    pub fn with_verbosity(mut self, verbosity: Verbosity) -> Self {
        self.verbosity = verbosity;
        self
    }

    pub fn is_quiet(&self) -> bool {
        self.verbosity == Verbosity::Quiet
    }

    pub fn is_verbose(&self) -> bool {
        self.verbosity >= Verbosity::Verbose
    }

    pub fn is_debug(&self) -> bool {
        self.verbosity >= Verbosity::Debug
    }

    /// Print only if not quiet
    pub fn print_normal(&self, text: &str) {
        if self.verbosity >= Verbosity::Normal {
            self.print(text);
        }
    }

    /// Print only in verbose mode
    pub fn print_verbose(&self, text: &str) {
        if self.is_verbose() {
            if self.is_styled() {
                self.print(&format!("[{}][verbose][/] {}", self.theme.muted, text));
            } else {
                println!("[verbose] {}", text);
            }
        }
    }

    /// Print only in debug mode
    pub fn print_debug(&self, text: &str) {
        if self.is_debug() {
            if self.is_styled() {
                self.print(&format!("[{}][debug][/] {}", self.theme.muted, text));
            } else {
                println!("[debug] {}", text);
            }
        }
    }

    /// Initialize tracing based on verbosity level
    pub fn init_tracing(&self) {
        use tracing_subscriber::EnvFilter;

        let filter = EnvFilter::new(self.verbosity.log_filter());
        tracing_subscriber::fmt()
            .with_env_filter(filter)
            .with_writer(std::io::stderr)
            .init();
    }
}
```

### CLI Integration
```rust
// In src/main.rs (clap args)
#[derive(Parser)]
struct Args {
    /// Quiet mode - suppress non-error output
    #[arg(short, long, global = true)]
    quiet: bool,

    /// Verbose mode - show extra details (-v for verbose, -vv for debug)
    #[arg(short, long, global = true, action = clap::ArgAction::Count)]
    verbose: u8,

    // ... other args
}

// In main()
let verbosity = Verbosity::from_flags(args.quiet, args.verbose);
let output = Output::new(args.format).with_verbosity(verbosity);

// Initialize tracing for debug output
if verbosity >= Verbosity::Debug {
    output.init_tracing();
}
```

### Behavior Matrix
| Flag | Progress | Warnings | Errors | Details | Debug/Trace |
|------|----------|----------|--------|---------|-------------|
| (none) | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| -q | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| -v | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ |
| -vv | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |

### Quiet Mode Effects
- Progress bars: Hidden
- Spinners: Hidden
- Info messages: Hidden
- Warnings: Hidden (only errors shown)
- Success messages: Hidden
- Only final output (JSON/CSV/text results) printed
- Tracing: ERROR level only

### Verbose Mode Effects
- Error panels show --details section
- Index command shows per-file progress
- Search shows query analysis breakdown
- Stats shows additional metrics
- Doctor shows check details
- Tracing: INFO level

### Debug Mode Effects
- All verbose output
- Query parse tree displayed
- Index timing breakdown per phase
- Memory usage stats
- Stack traces on errors
- Tracing: DEBUG level (full trace output)

### JSON/CSV Output Behavior
Verbosity flags DO NOT affect structured output formats:
- JSON output: Always machine-readable, no progress/debug text mixed in
- CSV output: Always clean rows, no progress/debug text mixed in
- Progress/debug goes to stderr when format is JSON/CSV

```rust
impl Output {
    /// Print to appropriate stream based on format
    pub fn print_progress(&self, text: &str) {
        if self.is_quiet() {
            return;
        }

        // For structured formats, progress goes to stderr
        if matches!(self.format, OutputFormat::Json | OutputFormat::Csv) {
            eprintln!("{}", text);
        } else {
            self.print(text);
        }
    }
}
```

