Without a rigorous harness, model selection is subjective. This harness ensures **reproducible**, **decision-grade** comparisons and produces logs usable for regression analysis.

## Metrics to Measure

### Speed Metrics
1. Cold load time
2. Warm latency p50/p95/p99
3. Batch throughput (1/8/32/128)
4. Sustained throughput (5 min test)
5. Time-to-first-result (TTFR)

### Memory Metrics
1. Model file size
2. Peak RSS during load
3. Steady-state RSS
4. RSS under load

### Quality Metrics
1. NDCG@10
2. MRR@10
3. Recall@1/5/10/100
4. Latency-adjusted quality score

### Reliability Metrics
1. Error rate (failed embeddings)
2. OOM thresholds
3. Graceful fallback rate

## Test Datasets
- `xf-twitter-sample` (tweets)
- `xf-dm-sample` (DMs)
- `cass-session-sample` (coding transcripts)
- `synthetic-stress` (edge cases)

